 I guess it depends upon your perspective. If you are Joe Blow citizen with no connections, yeah, 2000+ people over the last 2.5 years does not seem too bad. If you are the mother or father of one of the men or women who was killed, you might take a different stance. I doubt many of these families who have lost loved ones are jumping up and down in the streets about the low death toll. The only difference is we have a lot fewer families who have lost loved ones in thisw war as compared to other wars in our past. This however does not diminish the pain of those who have lost friends or loved ones. 

